License: UNKNOWN
Description: py-jail
        =======
        
        A native Python wrapper for FreeBSD jails using libc.
        
        ## Usage
        
        ### jail_set
        
        ```python
        >>> import jail
        >>> jiov = jail.Jiov(dict(persist=None, jid=23, path="/rescue"))
        >>> jail.dll.jail_set(jiov.pointer, len(jiov), 1)
        23
        ```
        
        ### jail_remove
        
        ```python
        >>> import jail
        >>> jiov = jail.Jiov(dict(persist=None, jid=23, path="/rescue"))
        >>> jail.dll.jail_remove(23)
        -1
        >>> jail.dll.jail_set(jiov.pointer, len(jiov), 1)
        23
        >>> jail.dll.jail_set(jiov.pointer, len(jiov), 1)
        -1
        >>> jiov.errmsg.value
        b'jail 23 already exists'
        >>> jail.dll.jail_remove(23)
        0
        >>> jail.dll.jail_set(jiov.pointer, len(jiov), 1)
        23
        ```
Platform: UNKNOWN
Requires-Python: >=3.6
